1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:03,510
(Episode 114)

2
00:00:25,130 --> 00:00:26,130
Oh my...

3
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,300
Jung Suk Hee.

4
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:32,740
How dare you steal Ma Eun Hye's necklace?

5
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:37,480
You knew I was the Chairman's daughter.

6
00:00:38,140 --> 00:00:39,640
Just because you stole my necklace,

7
00:00:40,010 --> 00:00:43,050
do you think that will hide the fact
that I'm Ma Eun Hye?

8
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:45,120
No.

9
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:47,890
As if killing my daughter, Seo Rin,
wasn't enough,

10
00:00:48,450 --> 00:00:50,390
you even hid the fact
that I was Ma Eun Hye.

11
00:00:50,660 --> 00:00:51,890
Are you even human?

12
00:00:52,660 --> 00:00:56,130
- You rummaged through my room?
- It's over for you.

13
00:00:56,830 --> 00:01:00,400
My father is Chairman Ma Dae Chang
of Dream Group.

14
00:01:00,470 --> 00:01:03,030
- And I am his daughter.
- No!

15
00:01:04,740 --> 00:01:07,270
Bring my daughter back to life!
Bring her back!

16
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:11,580
Please, stop. It wasn't me.
Jung Suk Hee, you're mistaken.

17
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:12,710
It's not true.

18
00:01:15,550 --> 00:01:18,320
I'll make you pay for what you did to me.

19
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:19,320
Die.

20
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:22,350
Do you really think your son can live well
after you killed Seo Rin?

21
00:01:22,350 --> 00:01:24,220
Let go!

22
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:31,030
Fine. You think I'll go down that easily?
In your dreams!

23
00:01:31,130 --> 00:01:33,900
I'll make you pay for everything
all at once.

24
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:37,240
Go ahead, keep barking.

25
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:40,210
But you'll still be the one
losing in the end.

26
00:01:43,010 --> 00:01:46,850
You let Seo Rin die, didn't you?
You should die too!

27
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:50,650
- Die! Just die!
- Stop!

28
00:01:50,650 --> 00:01:52,650
You're asking me what you can do?

29
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:54,950
Get out of my sight. Just disappear!

30
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:56,320
Die!

31
00:01:56,390 --> 00:01:58,490
- Stop... Please help me.
- Die!

32
00:01:58,660 --> 00:01:59,890
Help me.

33
00:02:01,860 --> 00:02:02,860
What are you doing?

34
00:02:03,460 --> 00:02:04,760
Are you falling asleep on the stairs?

35
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:06,970
What?

36
00:02:08,130 --> 00:02:09,200
Jung Suk Hee.

37
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,440
Where's Jung Suk Hee?

38
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:20,810
An antihistamine?

39
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:23,880
That's for allergies.

40
00:02:23,880 --> 00:02:25,720
Where's Jung Suk Hee? Where is she?

41
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,450
- Let go of me!
- Why are you so desperate to find my mom?

42
00:02:28,850 --> 00:02:29,850
Let go of me!

43
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:32,520
Why did you and your mother come here?

44
00:02:33,090 --> 00:02:35,760
Is it a problem that I'm here?
I'm the Chairman's granddaughter.

45
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:38,760
Come on, just lock.

46
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,760
Chae Hwa Young.

47
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:42,200
Now that Seo Rin is gone,

48
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,700
shouldn't you be the one
to leave this house?

49
00:02:43,770 --> 00:02:44,840
Where's your mother?

50
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:48,670
Jung Suk Hee has her memory back, right?

51
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,320
Where's Jung Suk Hee?

52
00:03:00,390 --> 00:03:01,450
Where's Jung Suk Hee?

53
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:05,690
- Why are you so desperate to find my mom?
- Jung Suk Hee!

54
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,330
Suk Hee is pooping.

55
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:13,930
Mom, why use Chae Hwa Young's bathroom?

56
00:03:13,930 --> 00:03:15,070
Seriously...

57
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:17,170
You could've just used the one downstairs.

58
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:19,700
I like the thief's bathroom.

59
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:23,610
- It smells nice in here.
- For crying out loud. You're ridiculous.

60
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:25,180
Mom, let's get out of here.

61
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:31,850
- Thief!
- Shut up! Don't you ever say that again!

62
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:53,640
(Chang)

63
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:55,370
This thing gave me a heart attack.

64
00:03:58,580 --> 00:03:59,580
What?

65
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:03,180
You're saying Chae Hwa Young
had Seo Rin's newborn clothes?

66
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:06,580
Yes. She kept them in a locked drawer.

67
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:10,390
And there seemed to be something else
under them,

68
00:04:10,390 --> 00:04:12,690
but I couldn't check
because Chae Hwa Young showed up.

69
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:17,600
Also, I think Chae Hwa Young
might have some kind of allergy.

70
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:20,700
I saw a bottle of antihistamines
on her vanity.

71
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:23,270
Chae Hwa Young has allergies?

72
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:28,440
That bastard doctor who killed our Seo Rin
filed to close his clinic?

73
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:32,280
- Yes.
- It's not like the closure is immediate.

74
00:04:32,380 --> 00:04:35,380
There are legal procedures,
so it'll probably take a month or two.

75
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:39,580
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho is often at the clinic
to gather evidence.

76
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,890
Have you confirmed
where Chae Hwa Young was at that time?

77
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:45,860
I've confirmed she was in Seoul
at that time.

78
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:49,960
It doesn't seem like CEO Chae
is connected to Director Ma's death.

79
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:55,470
For now, they might destroy evidence
and run,

80
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:58,840
- so keep a close eye on them.
- Yes, sir.

81
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:08,010
I can't let my dear Seo Rin's death
have been in vain.

82
00:05:08,810 --> 00:05:13,180
Something definitely happened
at that clinic.

83
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:16,990
Yes, I understand.

84
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,360
Okay.

85
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:22,160
Who was that on the phone?

86
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,600
Things are getting interesting.

87
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:27,830
What's going on?

88
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,570
That was my source at the Hills Hotel.

89
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:34,010
Hills Hotel?

90
00:05:34,610 --> 00:05:37,040
They're Dream Hotel's biggest rival.

91
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,480
I heard they've been having
financial trouble lately.

92
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:42,750
Hills Hotel,
which is the crown jewel of Hills Group,

93
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:44,480
will be put up for sale soon.

94
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:47,020
I knew this would happen to Hills Group.

95
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:51,360
- Their reckless expansion led to this.
- Hills Hotel...

96
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:54,530
What if we acquire it?

97
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:57,630
We could acquire it...

98
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:00,930
and merge Dream and Hills Hotels.

99
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:04,000
And then we can launch a new brand
called Dream Hills.

100
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:06,000
As your very own hotel.

101
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:10,170
It's a tempting offer,
but money's the issue.

102
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,780
The slush fund? Absolutely not.

103
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,080
The source of those funds
isn't transparent.

104
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,650
If we use this cash recklessly...

105
00:06:17,650 --> 00:06:20,690
and the authorities start tracking it,

106
00:06:20,690 --> 00:06:22,120
how would we even handle that?

107
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:24,560
You don't run a business
with your own money.

108
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,460
You know that.

109
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,330
Bank loans and...

110
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,160
Investors?

111
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,130
Exactly.

112
00:06:33,130 --> 00:06:35,000
We bring in some solid investors.

113
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:38,970
That's how we create your very own hotel.

114
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,810
So, Jun Ho made that kind of proposal?

115
00:06:45,980 --> 00:06:49,880
Yes. He says I should launch
a new high-end brand.

116
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:51,950
He said that it's a way...

117
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:53,890
to escape Chairman Ma's
old-fashioned management style...

118
00:06:54,150 --> 00:06:58,120
and that it would be our winning move,
using a fresh and innovative approach.

119
00:06:58,490 --> 00:06:59,890
Thriving in a crisis.

120
00:06:59,890 --> 00:07:01,230
He really takes after you.

121
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:03,660
I'll start looking for investors
right away.

122
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,400
Weren't there a few wealthy investors...

123
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:09,030
on the guest list for the bonsai show?

124
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:11,140
- Get me that list.
- Yes.

125
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:15,370
By the way,
what's your plan for Jung Suk Hee?

126
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:17,540
Why are you bringing her up
and ruining the mood?

127
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,680
If Chairman Ma finds out
Jung Suk Hee is Ma Eun Hye,

128
00:07:20,210 --> 00:07:22,410
it'll be a disaster, won't it?

129
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:26,680
Find out how far Secretary Kim has gotten,

130
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:30,620
and prepare our response accordingly.
Got it?

131
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:32,420
Understood.

132
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:37,200
Baek Ho.

133
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:40,460
Is everything okay? You look so down.

134
00:07:41,270 --> 00:07:44,170
I just came back from the police station.

135
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,870
What about the plastic surgeon?

136
00:07:46,370 --> 00:07:47,670
Did you find anything out?

137
00:07:47,940 --> 00:07:51,980
No. It looks like they're wrapping it up
as malpractice by the surgeon.

138
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:54,380
Before they close the case,

139
00:07:54,810 --> 00:07:57,010
we have to find the nurse
who was in the operating room.

140
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:58,780
We have to.

141
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:05,020
It's my mom.

142
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:09,160
I'll get going then. See you later.

143
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,200
Hey, Mom.

144
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:19,540
Son.

145
00:08:20,540 --> 00:08:22,810
I just called because
I wanted to hear your voice.

146
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:24,910
Come on, Mom.

147
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,610
We saw each other this morning.
Why are you calling already?

148
00:08:31,050 --> 00:08:32,950
I'm okay, Mom.

149
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,320
I know...

150
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:37,020
you must be feeling so unsettled.

151
00:08:37,190 --> 00:08:38,420
But, Baek Ho,

152
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:41,390
nothing has changed.

153
00:08:42,130 --> 00:08:44,630
We can just keep on living
the way we always have.

154
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,100
The fact...

155
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:49,200
that you are my son...

156
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,400
would never change,
even if the world turned upside down.

157
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,440
You know that, right?

158
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,610
Of course I do.

159
00:08:57,010 --> 00:08:58,310
I'm your son.

160
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:59,740
If you are curious...

161
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:03,050
about how you came to be with us,

162
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:04,750
you can ask me anytime.

163
00:09:05,780 --> 00:09:07,820
If you want to know about your roots,

164
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:10,550
I'll do everything I can to help you.

165
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:14,030
No. I don't really want to find them.

166
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:16,890
Because if I do,

167
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:21,000
it would feel like
I'm really not your son.

168
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:23,230
And I don't want that.

169
00:09:25,270 --> 00:09:27,570
Baek Ho, just remember one thing.

170
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:31,740
I'm always on your side,
and you know that, right?

171
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:32,880
I know.

172
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:37,480
Can you make me
some spicy stir-fried squid?

173
00:09:39,050 --> 00:09:40,450
Okay, you got it.

174
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:43,220
I'll make the spicy stir-fried squid
my son loves so much.

175
00:09:45,690 --> 00:09:46,690
Mom.

176
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:50,800
I love you.

177
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:54,700
I love you too, son.

178
00:09:57,070 --> 00:09:58,070
Talk to you later.

179
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:13,450
So it turns out, we're not related at all.

180
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:15,320
What's your point?

181
00:10:15,650 --> 00:10:19,090
You were still my parents' son,

182
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:22,030
so I always felt this nagging debt to you,
which bothered me.

183
00:10:22,690 --> 00:10:24,200
But now? It's a huge weight
off my shoulders.

184
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:26,360
It means no matter what I do to you,

185
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:30,130
I don't have to feel a shred of guilt.

186
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,600
The feeling's mutual.

187
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:35,070
I'm warning you one last time.
Don't do anything stupid.

188
00:10:35,470 --> 00:10:36,640
I'm done holding back.

189
00:10:37,410 --> 00:10:38,710
Then let me make one thing crystal clear.

190
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:44,820
The woman you love, Oh Jang Mi, is dead.

191
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:50,490
- What?
- And the woman who works here...

192
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,290
is Director Ma Seo Rin.

193
00:10:53,220 --> 00:10:55,460
- And she's going to marry me.
- Kang Jun Ho!

194
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:58,160
Are you still that delusional?

195
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,460
We're married.
We're already husband and wife!

196
00:11:02,770 --> 00:11:04,270
Haven't you seen our parents?

197
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:06,570
They're married,
but they live like strangers.

198
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:09,540
You think your love will last forever?

199
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:14,110
I’m going to show you firsthand
how even a love you can’t live without...

200
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:15,450
can fall apart in an instant.

201
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:18,050
Then here's one last piece of advice,
as your former brother.

202
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,420
What you feel isn't love.
It's obsession and greed.

203
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:22,750
The moment you risk everything
for your greed,

204
00:11:23,420 --> 00:11:24,420
you'll eventually...

205
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:26,420
be destroyed by the same greed.

206
00:11:27,060 --> 00:11:28,060
Mark my words.

207
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:32,930
We'll see about that, Kang Baek Ho.

208
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:36,030
I don't know who your parents are,

209
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,170
but this game is already over.

210
00:11:40,270 --> 00:11:43,870
Just remember whoever gets her first wins.

211
00:11:47,650 --> 00:11:48,650
Manager Lee.

212
00:11:49,450 --> 00:11:50,510
I have a great idea.

213
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:55,390
- What is it? Did you find an investor?
- No, that can wait.

214
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:59,460
First, we need to get that eyesore,
Jung Suk Hee, out of the picture.

215
00:11:59,660 --> 00:12:01,590
What? But how?

216
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:04,800
If Jung Suk Hee so much as mentions
the necklace,

217
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:08,300
the four-leaf clover,
or the baby clothes to Chairman Ma,

218
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,070
it's only a matter of time
before we're exposed.

219
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:13,200
How will you get her out of the picture?

220
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:17,270
If Chairman Ma ends up in a crisis
because of that dim-witted Jung Suk Hee,

221
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:20,850
he'll never want to see her again.

222
00:12:21,380 --> 00:12:22,980
What exactly do you have in mind?

223
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:29,890
Yeom San Wol, I need you to run an errand.

224
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:36,460
Mom, are you holding up okay?

225
00:12:36,690 --> 00:12:39,730
I'm fine. It's what I do.

226
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:41,100
Look! The thief is here.

227
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:43,930
Look at the mother-daughter duo,
working hard to avoid getting kicked out.

228
00:12:44,070 --> 00:12:45,770
If you don't like what you see,
you can leave.

229
00:12:46,070 --> 00:12:49,310
After all, you used Seo Rin as an excuse
to come back to this house.

230
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:51,840
- You've overstayed your welcome. Get out.
- Shut up.

231
00:12:52,180 --> 00:12:55,580
You should be sucking up to me
if you don't want to get thrown out.

232
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:59,380
In this house, I'm second in command
after the Chairman. Got it?

233
00:12:59,450 --> 00:13:01,220
Who do you think you are
to be second to Grandfather?

234
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:03,690
You're not his daughter-in-law anymore,

235
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:05,620
and you're about
to lose your CEO position.

236
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,190
So brace yourself.
Your days here are numbered.

237
00:13:08,790 --> 00:13:12,300
- Get out. Stop bothering my mother.
- You get out.

238
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:15,370
I came here to speak to her.

239
00:13:16,330 --> 00:13:19,100
Yeom San Wol bought
this organic pomegranate extract...

240
00:13:19,470 --> 00:13:21,240
for the Chairman.

241
00:13:23,110 --> 00:13:25,780
Oh Jang Mi.
Relax, I'm not going to eat her alive.

242
00:13:26,610 --> 00:13:27,980
Are you just going to stand there
and watch?

243
00:13:28,210 --> 00:13:30,110
Why are you trying to get me
away from my mom?

244
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:31,680
What are you plotting now?

245
00:13:31,850 --> 00:13:34,220
What are you talking about?
What would I be plotting?

246
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,990
Watch what you say.

247
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:37,450
Seo Rin.

248
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:40,220
I mean, Jang Mi...

249
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:41,560
Gosh, it's so confusing.

250
00:13:41,930 --> 00:13:43,930
Come on out.
The Chairman is asking for you.

251
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:45,960
Okay, I'm coming.

252
00:13:54,610 --> 00:13:55,640
Jung Suk Hee, listen closely.

253
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:59,940
You know what? Never mind.
Let me just show you.

254
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:06,450
(Ma)

255
00:14:06,650 --> 00:14:07,650
Look.

256
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:12,490
This one is only for the Chairman.
See? It's marked here on the bottle.

257
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,290
- Yes.
- Look.

258
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:20,200
Pour this much into a shot glass.

259
00:14:22,170 --> 00:14:23,170
Okay?

260
00:14:23,870 --> 00:14:26,670
And then add 150 milliliters of water.

261
00:14:26,970 --> 00:14:28,910
You have to add three times
as much water as concentrate.

262
00:14:29,470 --> 00:14:30,710
Okay, three times.

263
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,280
Three times...

264
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,650
Right, three times.

265
00:14:38,180 --> 00:14:39,580
Right. You're getting it.

266
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,550
And here's an unopened one.

267
00:14:42,550 --> 00:14:43,720
You open it like this,

268
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:49,230
pour it in the glass,
and add ice water just like before.

269
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:54,200
Okay. I can do this. I'm doing great.

270
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:55,830
Yes, like this.

271
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,200
Don't mix up the Chairman's bottle
with the ones for the rest of the family.

272
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,840
I won't get them mixed up.

273
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:04,210
This one is the Chairman's.

274
00:15:04,580 --> 00:15:08,610
Right. The one with "Ma" on it
is for the Chairman, all right?

275
00:15:09,580 --> 00:15:13,080
Gosh, I wonder if you can even read.

276
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:16,490
- I can't read.
- That's just great.

277
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:19,120
Look closely. The Chairman's bottle...

278
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:22,660
See? This one, with this little coaster,
is the Chairman's. Got it?

279
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:24,030
Don't get them mixed up.

280
00:15:24,530 --> 00:15:27,870
Make sure you serve it to the Chairman
exactly like this, okay?

281
00:15:27,930 --> 00:15:30,430
Okay. I can do a good job.

282
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:31,770
I can do this.

283
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:34,070
All right,
let's see you do a good job, okay?

284
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:35,840
Now, go mix it well and bring it out.

285
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:56,590
Why are we having juice?
We're about to eat dinner.

286
00:15:57,160 --> 00:16:00,660
For your health, I bought
some cold-pressed pomegranate juice.

287
00:16:00,830 --> 00:16:02,670
The organic kind, no less.

288
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:06,740
It was a special import and hard to get,
so I had San Wol rush out to buy it.

289
00:16:06,970 --> 00:16:07,970
Juice?

290
00:16:08,370 --> 00:16:10,670
What is Chae Hwa Young up to now?

291
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:12,140
Suk Hee, bring them over.

292
00:16:13,010 --> 00:16:14,010
Yes.

293
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,020
Here you go.

294
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,770
Why didn't you bring a glass for yourself,
Suk Hee?

295
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:37,570
I already had some.

296
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:40,870
- It's so delicious.
- The color is lovely.

297
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:44,940
- Isn't this good for women's health, too?
- Right, I've heard...

298
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:48,810
pomegranate is good for the health
of middle-aged women,

299
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:51,480
but I wonder if it will do any good
for someone like me.

300
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:55,820
Of course. It's also called
the blood vessel cleanser.

301
00:16:56,150 --> 00:16:58,160
The antioxidants in it...

302
00:16:58,460 --> 00:17:00,990
are said to naturally
lower blood pressure.

303
00:17:01,390 --> 00:17:05,100
When I saw you collapse last time,

304
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:07,230
I was so terribly shocked and worried.

305
00:17:07,730 --> 00:17:10,530
- That's why I told her to buy it.
- What’s gotten into you,

306
00:17:10,870 --> 00:17:12,240
caring about me like this?

307
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,670
I just took my blood pressure medication
a little while ago.

308
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:21,210
In that case, Grandfather,
you should drink this after your meal.

309
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:25,080
Besides, having something sweet
before a meal isn't good for you.

310
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:26,780
It's actually better to have it now.

311
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:29,690
Something sweet will actually
stimulate your appetite.

312
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:34,590
Besides, pomegranate has no ingredients
that affect blood pressure medicine,

313
00:17:34,690 --> 00:17:37,060
so it's fine to have it
even after taking your medicine.

314
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:41,030
If you're that doubtful,
you can look it up online.

315
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:45,400
All right. Then let's give it a try.

316
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:49,470
I've been craving something tart, anyway.

317
00:17:49,710 --> 00:17:52,240
While we're at it,
let's have a toast, honey.

318
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:56,910
All right, everyone.
To our health. Cheers!

319
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:58,220
- Okay.
- Here.

320
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:01,450
Cheers.

321
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:06,190
Jung Suk Hee.

322
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:09,390
Soon, you could be charged
for attempted murder.

323
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:12,000
(Ma)

324
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,830
This one looks a bit cloudy.

325
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:19,340
Did you mix
the grapefruit concentrate in properly?

326
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,470
Yes. Even a small amount of grapefruit...

327
00:18:21,470 --> 00:18:24,040
is potent enough to block
the enzymes in blood pressure medication.

328
00:18:24,740 --> 00:18:28,310
This should be more than enough
to induce pharmacological shock.

329
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,520
But the Chairman’s bottle
is already unsealed.

330
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:34,080
Won't Jung Suk Hee get suspicious?

331
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:36,750
Jung Suk Hee is a dimwit.
She won't notice.

332
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:39,320
After he drinks the pomegranate juice
with grapefruit...

333
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:40,590
that Jung Suk Hee prepares,

334
00:18:40,790 --> 00:18:42,890
and Chairman Ma collapses
from a heart issue,

335
00:18:43,530 --> 00:18:44,960
San Wol and I will go to the kitchen,

336
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:49,530
pretend we found the grapefruit bottle
to expose her. That's the plan.

337
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:53,370
Jung Suk Hee cooks for a living,
so she knows a lot about ingredients.

338
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,770
- You just have to emphasize that.
- Right.

339
00:18:57,210 --> 00:19:00,440
The story is that Jung Suk Hee knows
grapefruit is bad for high blood pressure.

340
00:19:00,610 --> 00:19:04,080
So she deliberately mixed this
only into the Chairman's bottle...

341
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:05,850
to try and kill him.

342
00:19:06,850 --> 00:19:10,690
She planned to get revenge
for what happened with Dong Seok.

343
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:14,390
But can Jung Suk Hee tell the bottles
apart and serve the right one?

344
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:17,490
I only put the grapefruit concentrate
in Chairman Ma's bottle.

345
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:21,400
This bottle here
is just pure pomegranate concentrate.

346
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:24,430
- But what if...
- I'll make it foolproof for her.

347
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:25,440
Don't worry.

348
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:28,970
Besides, I had Yeom San Wol buy
the pomegranate concentrate,

349
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:30,540
so no one will suspect me.

350
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:32,880
Here you go.

351
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,110
Okay, thanks.

352
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:36,250
You can go.

353
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,840
Oh my.

354
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:06,780
This is refreshing. It's quite good.

355
00:20:07,310 --> 00:20:08,980
I feel healthier already.

356
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,550
I should have this more often.

357
00:20:11,750 --> 00:20:13,320
It's really good.

358
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:15,550
Suk Hee did a good job.

359
00:20:16,490 --> 00:20:19,760
Chairman Ma should be collapsing
from the shock any second now.

360
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:24,490
So long. This must be what they call
killing two birds with one stone.

361
00:20:24,830 --> 00:20:26,600
Grandfather, are you feeling okay?

362
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,970
You said you took
your blood pressure medication earlier.

363
00:20:29,070 --> 00:20:32,800
I'm fine.
In fact, I feel sharper than ever.

364
00:20:33,670 --> 00:20:35,740
What?
Why is Chairman Ma reacting like this?

365
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:38,710
He should be feeling dizzy
or getting a headache by now.

366
00:20:39,310 --> 00:20:42,650
That's strange.
I'm certain I prepared his drink myself.

367
00:20:43,310 --> 00:20:44,350
That dimwit.

368
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:46,650
I told her exactly which one.
Did she grab the other one?

369
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:51,290
Wait a minute.
My juice tasted a little bitter.

370
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:52,890
No way...

371
00:20:58,460 --> 00:20:59,760
Hwa Young, what's wrong with you?

372
00:21:02,930 --> 00:21:04,600
What's the matter?

373
00:21:05,470 --> 00:21:08,240
Oh my gosh, that's right.
Hwa Young has allergies.

374
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:09,570
You...

375
00:21:09,570 --> 00:21:11,210
Jung Suk Hee.

376
00:21:11,910 --> 00:21:13,010
- What?
- Jung Suk Hee!

377
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:15,110
Suk Hee did nothing wrong.

378
00:21:15,910 --> 00:21:18,220
The thief, Chae Hwa Young, is dying.
She can't breathe.

379
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:19,250
Oh my, what's wrong with her?

380
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:20,980
It's agony, isn't it, Chae Hwa Young?

381
00:21:21,450 --> 00:21:25,190
You're allergic to grapefruit.
You tried to kill the Chairman,

382
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,890
but you fell into your own trap,
Chae Hwa Young.

383
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,230
Oh my gosh!

384
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:34,730
What is wrong with her?

385
00:21:34,730 --> 00:21:37,930
Oh my gosh, what do we do?
Oh, dear. Hey, get it together!

386
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,040
Oh my goodness!

387
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:43,010
See? This one, with this little coaster,
is the Chairman's. Got it?

388
00:21:43,110 --> 00:21:44,240
Don't get them mixed up.

389
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:48,050
Make sure you serve it to the Chairman
exactly like this, okay?

390
00:21:48,050 --> 00:21:50,080
Okay. I can do a good job.

391
00:21:50,150 --> 00:21:51,550
I can do this.

392
00:21:52,150 --> 00:21:53,920
All right,
let's see you do a good job, okay?

393
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:55,490
Now, go mix it well and bring it out.

394
00:22:25,420 --> 00:22:26,420
Chae Hwa Young.

395
00:22:27,020 --> 00:22:29,750
What is this?
Why did she hide it here and leave?

396
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:33,890
Wait a minute.
They're both pomegranate extract,

397
00:22:34,090 --> 00:22:36,830
but why did she tell me
to open one for the Chairman...

398
00:22:37,130 --> 00:22:40,560
and serve the other one
to the rest of the family?

399
00:22:42,070 --> 00:22:44,300
Why not just open one bottle for everyone?

400
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,340
Why would she bother separating them?

401
00:23:03,850 --> 00:23:04,860
What is it?

402
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:08,690
She mixed something
into the Chairman's pomegranate juice.

403
00:23:09,230 --> 00:23:11,030
The taste is subtly different.

404
00:23:13,530 --> 00:23:14,530
Wait a minute.

405
00:23:14,970 --> 00:23:17,800
It's like some other fruit extract
was mixed in.

406
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:30,180
It's grapefruit. It's grapefruit extract.

407
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:33,780
Chae Hwa Young, that wicked woman.

408
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,990
They say grapefruit is bad for people
with high blood pressure.

409
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:38,490
She was going to make the Chairman
drink this extract...

410
00:23:38,790 --> 00:23:40,490
to make him collapse.

411
00:23:41,690 --> 00:23:44,590
And then she was going to frame me for it.

412
00:23:45,730 --> 00:23:46,930
The nerve of her.

413
00:23:47,660 --> 00:23:48,670
Mom.

414
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,230
I heard Chae Hwa Young
is allergic to grapefruit.

415
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:54,100
Apparently, if she eats it,
she gets hives and her face swells up,

416
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,610
and in severe cases,
she even has difficulty breathing.

417
00:23:57,040 --> 00:24:00,440
That's why she carries an antihistamine
just in case.

418
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:04,010
I had no idea Chae Hwa Young
had an allergy like that.

419
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:15,930
Chae Hwa Young.
This is going to be very painful.

420
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:18,030
Let's see how you like
a taste of your own medicine.

421
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:20,600
Oh my gosh.

422
00:24:24,470 --> 00:24:26,740
Hello, 911? Someone here...

423
00:24:29,310 --> 00:24:31,170
- My goodness.
- What are we going to do?

424
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:35,550
There's something suspicious
about that hospital.

425
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:38,950
How could they start shutting down
right after Seo Rin's accident?

426
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:42,350
I should've investigated the OR
more thoroughly.

427
00:24:46,260 --> 00:24:47,360
What are you doing, son?

428
00:24:47,690 --> 00:24:49,160
Nothing.

429
00:24:50,090 --> 00:24:51,230
What's that?

430
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:53,860
Go ahead and open it.

431
00:24:58,130 --> 00:24:59,300
What is this?

432
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:04,110
Back when I first adopted you,

433
00:25:04,540 --> 00:25:06,110
the person who left you
at the orphanage...

434
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:08,180
left this along with you.

435
00:25:09,450 --> 00:25:11,980
You're saying I wore this tiny thing
when I arrived at the orphanage?

436
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:21,060
This is a golden spoon.

437
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:24,160
It's so shiny and bright.
Do you think this is real gold?

438
00:25:24,630 --> 00:25:26,300
I heard the price of gold
has gone up a lot lately.

439
00:25:28,330 --> 00:25:30,230
I bet this would sell for a lot.

440
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:34,170
But what's this here?

441
00:25:34,670 --> 00:25:38,510
- It looks like some kind of crest.
- I don't know what that is either.

442
00:25:38,740 --> 00:25:42,410
The person who left you at the orphanage
included it with you.

443
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:46,680
It probably has something to do
with your family roots.

444
00:25:46,950 --> 00:25:50,350
Judging by this, I must have come
from a super rich family.

445
00:25:51,390 --> 00:25:55,430
But if I was from a rich family,
why was I sent to an orphanage?

446
00:25:55,990 --> 00:25:58,630
Even when I first saw you,
you were just a little baby,

447
00:25:58,930 --> 00:26:02,870
but you had this noble air about you
that just lit up the entire room.

448
00:26:02,930 --> 00:26:06,800
Right? Then and now,
I'm the definition of class.

449
00:26:08,270 --> 00:26:09,270
Baek Ho.

450
00:26:10,670 --> 00:26:14,410
You don't have to force yourself
to look cheerful.

451
00:26:14,980 --> 00:26:16,250
I know how you're feeling.

452
00:26:16,780 --> 00:26:18,750
You must be so confused.

453
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:23,850
For over 30 years, you believed
we were your birth parents,

454
00:26:24,990 --> 00:26:28,860
so it must feel like your whole world
has been uprooted overnight.

455
00:26:30,690 --> 00:26:34,700
If you're confused and hurting,
it's okay to say so, Baek Ho.

456
00:26:35,730 --> 00:26:38,800
I'm your mother. I'll always understand.

457
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:41,710
I'm okay.

458
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:46,810
But thank you for saying that, Mom.

459
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,510
If you're curious,

460
00:26:50,210 --> 00:26:53,520
I can introduce you to the director
of the orphanage we adopted you from.

461
00:26:53,580 --> 00:26:55,050
You don't have to do that.

462
00:26:55,420 --> 00:26:58,050
Like I said, I'm happy
with my life as it is.

463
00:26:59,260 --> 00:27:00,390
Aren't you curious at all?

464
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:04,190
I'm not some angsty teen.
I'm past all that.

465
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:08,160
What's the point of digging up the past?
You're the only mom I need.

466
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:11,970
That's my boy.

467
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:15,610
You're such a blessing.

468
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:19,310
There's no one like my son, Baek Ho.

469
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:23,250
Still, if you ever get curious later on,

470
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:25,820
you can always come and talk to me, okay?

471
00:27:27,250 --> 00:27:29,250
- I will.
- Okay.

472
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:43,600
Wait. I feel like I've seen
this crest before.

473
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:46,470
Where could it have been?

474
00:27:48,510 --> 00:27:51,810
(Ma)

475
00:27:58,150 --> 00:28:01,350
Oh my gosh, what do we do?

476
00:28:02,420 --> 00:28:03,820
Oh my goodness.

477
00:28:09,230 --> 00:28:11,160
Chae Hwa Young.

478
00:28:14,430 --> 00:28:16,030
What in the world...

479
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:19,800
was she trying to pull?

480
00:28:43,730 --> 00:28:45,230
(The First Man)

481
00:28:45,430 --> 00:28:48,060
Don't tell me you're
with Lawyer Han Young Ja.

482
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:51,170
If you keep this up, I'll have to
take matters into my own hands.

483
00:28:51,570 --> 00:28:53,370
Stop harassing my secretary.

484
00:28:53,770 --> 00:28:57,510
They're acquiring Hills Hotel?
They'd need hundreds of billions for that.

485
00:28:57,670 --> 00:29:01,610
They're probably looking for investors.
It's a ploy to swallow Dream Hotel whole.

486
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:05,180
I'll put my resignation on the line
to handle Chairman Ali myself.

487
00:29:05,650 --> 00:29:08,820
The CEO of Dream Hotel is so classless.

488
00:29:10,550 --> 00:29:12,560
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
